Easy Assembly: All hardware, tools, and instructions are included in the package, and all parts are labeled, allowing you to assemble them in 40 minutes. If you encounter any problems, it is recommended that you contact the appropriate customer service for professional help and advice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great table for the price!
reviews.reviewText: We bought this as a dining table. We like the finish and it's a great size! It was pretty easy to put together too. The most complicated part (the mechanism used to slide it out so you can put in the leaf) was already put together, so for people who struggle with instructions, it's easier than most. Pretty good quality. None of the terrible fake wood you screw stuff in either. It's all metal you screw things into, which is much better than most of this type of furniture you buy. Def recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for Small Space
reviews.reviewText: Product was packed well, easy assembly and looks great in small space.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good table for the price
reviews.reviewText: It’s a good low cost table, it was very easy to put together I think it took us about 30-45 minutes. The black is pretty, however this finish catches and holds finger prints and hand prints. All you have to do is barely touch it and you have prints so just know you will be wiping it down fairly often. The benches are really small. They are fine for kids, even bigger kids but not real practical for full size adults. 2 adults can sit on each bench but not very comfortably. My husband and I each weigh 175 lbs and they were just too thin for us so I bought a set of black chairs on Amazon, so for $300 I have a super nice set I’m happy with. The table and benches are very sturdy and seem like they will hold up for a long time. **NOTE** the benches DO fit under the table when it’s not extended. When the leaf is removed only the top slides. Not the entire frame of the table. I like this feature for space saving.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewText: We bought this table because we have a compact space in our dining area, and a medium sized family. We've got 3 kids- aged 12, 12, and 3. This table is amazing. It arrived beautifully packaged, has a tough table top, and the benches are wide enough to fit a bigger bottom, but small enough to sit nicely under the table. The leaf is sturdy and has a fantastic fit. It only took my husband and me 30 minutes to put together, and it's rock solid. The little corner protectors so that when our 3 year old is zooming around, he doesn't end up with bumps from the corners. It looks exactly like the picture. Fantastic table for the price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Is not scratch resistant. Very clearly shows fingerprints
reviews.reviewText: Not hard to assemble, except figuring out the rotary knob. Delivered on time; all pieces in tact. Seems sturdy. Is kind of low (H= 30in) for taller individuals. My daughter is 5’6; the table feels small / low to her. Definitely opens up space. Resembles a picnic table. Benches hold weight well (I’m a chunky one). Is NOT scratch resistant. I recommend a table cloth to preserve the newness and flawlessness. Shows ANY oil and FINGER PRINTS easily and immediately. Overall, worth the buy; not horribly expensive, not cheap enough to raise an eyebrow.
